{"article_id":"l3UZ9GiJIivYGGD6","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Obama administration once again is touting new data","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"showing job growth and another drop in the nation ' s unemployment rate ,","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"but beneath the surface lies a more bleak picture of the U.S. economy ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"as more and more Americans disappear from the labor force .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Last week ' s Department of Labor report said","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"the U.S. created more than 220,000 jobs in June ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"and the unemployment rate dropped to 5.3 percent , the lowest since the pre-Great Recession days of early 2008 .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Tucked within the study , however , is a figure","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"some analysts say","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"is far more important than month-to-month job figures :","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The number of Americans","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"working or searching for a job","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"has dropped to its lowest point in 38 years .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Just 62.6 percent of working-age Americans are participating in the labor force .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Participants are defined as those","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"who have a job","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"or are actively seeking one .","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"Those","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"who are not seeking work","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"are not counted in monthly jobless figures ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"meaning unemployment rates can fall","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"even though the number of Americans","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"getting paychecks","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"stays flat or drops .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"The troubling numbers cast doubt on the White House ' s continued claim","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"that Mr. Obama ' s policies have rescued the economy","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and put it on firm footing","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"moving forward .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Even some on the left say","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"the administration isn ' t acknowledging the true depth of the unemployment situation .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"While there is no doubt","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"there has been significant private sector job growth in recent years","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"- the economy has added 2.9 million jobs over the past year , for example -","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that growth , to some extent , masks bigger problems in the economy .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Data indicate","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that the biggest contributor to the shrinking U.S. labor pool is that fewer young Americans are working or actively seeking new jobs .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"The trend began more than 20 years ago ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"analysts say ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"and accelerated","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"after the recession began in 2008 .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"From 1995 to 2013 , the number of Americans","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"ages 15 to 24","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"participating in the labor force","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"fell by more than 11 percentage points ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"according to research from Ritholtz Wealth Management .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Labor force participation among those 25 to 54 years old also has fallen , though to a much lesser degree .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"At the same time , more older Americans are staying on the job","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"as they near retirement ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"though that hasn ' t been enough","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"to make up for the number of younger men and women","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"fleeing the workforce .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"\" If you look at the overarching trend ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"it does look like , over this 35-year period or so , young workers have been -","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"their labor force participation rates have been dropping , \"","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"said Elise Gould , senior economist at the Economic Policy Institute .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Ms. Gould pointed to data","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"showing","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that only about 55 percent of young Americans are working or looking for new jobs .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Contrary to popular belief ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"she said ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"most of those young people are not simply electing to remain in college .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"\" They ' re not sheltering in school .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"They ' re not seeing that as an alternative ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and they ' re not getting jobs in great numbers , \"","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Ms. Gould said .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"For its part , the administration continues to highlight positive numbers , such as the 223,000 jobs","depth":3},{"id":67,"text":"added in June in the health care , retail , business and other sectors of the economy .","depth":3},{"id":68,"text":"White House officials argue","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"that Mr. Obama ' s policies have saved the economy from the total collapse","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"it faced in 2008 and 2009 .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"They claim","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"Congress can accelerate growth","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"by enacting pieces of the president ' s agenda .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"\" Our economy has now added 5.6 million jobs over the past two years , the strongest two-year job growth since 2000 .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"despite this progress ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"there is more work to do , \"","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Betsey Stevenson , a member of the president ' s Council of Economic Advisers , said last week .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"\" We must continue to build on the positive trends","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"underlying our economy","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"by ensuring","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"that Americans","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"working overtime","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"receive a fair day ' s pay ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"opening new markets for U.S. goods and services through expanded trade ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"increasing investments in infrastructure ,","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"providing relief from the sequester","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"and raising the minimum wage . \"","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"But even fellow Democrats take issue with the White House ' s claims ,","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"and questions about the nation ' s true unemployment rate have crept into the 2016 presidential race .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"Sen. Bernard Sanders , a Vermont independent","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"seeking the White House as a Democrat ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"said Monday","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"that the administration ' s claim of a 5.3 percent unemployment rate doesn ' t hold water .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"\" There is another set of government statistics , \"","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"said the self-described socialist ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"\" and that real unemployment [ is ]","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"if you include those people","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"who have given up looking for work","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and the millions of others","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"who are working part-time , 20 , 25 hours a week","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"when they want to work full-time .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"When you put all of that together ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"real unemployment is 10.5 percent . \"","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Even those","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"who remain active participants in the labor force","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"and are seeking jobs on a daily basis","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"have found little success .","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"Robert Tognetti , 21 , a political science major and recent graduate of Marist College in New York , has relentlessly applied for jobs","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"since receiving his diploma from the liberal arts school in May .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"He says","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"he ' s applied to over 100 jobs , about five to six a day ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"but the tough job market has held him back .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"\" Having a college degree does not guarantee you a job anymore .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"There ' s still a lot of unemployed people .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"I know a lot of people","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"[ who were fired ]","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"trying to get back into the workforce ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"so it creates an environment","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"where the millennials are facing up against all the recently fired people , \"","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"\" I feel like each day it gets tougher to find a job , \"","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"he added .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":247,"left":189,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":127,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":125,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":147,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":129,"right":146,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":4,"right":128,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":146,"left":132,"right":14